            WHAT IT PUBLISHES. A STATED RULE and its OWN WORKED EXAMPLE OF THAT RULE.
            Rule, section IV.4.C, page label P-8, PDF p.12, verbatim: "PCB(s) shall be checked open
            before operating isolating devices." A flat imperative. No arithmetic, no tolerance, no
            convention: a sequence either honors it or it does not. THAT IS THE GATE.
            Worked example, section X.2 Example 1, page label P-45, PDF p.49: the Central-East Columbia
            No. 3 230 kV line is de-energized "by opening PCBs A-10 and A-3 by supervisory control",
            and only THEN are the isolating disconnects operated and tagged. The document applies its
            own rule to a named circuit with named devices. Same shape as 02's manual agreeing with
            itself three ways.
            The illustration is a DEVICE LEVEL one line, rendered at 3x and read as an image rather
            than inferred from the text layer: PCB A-10 with a disconnect either side + ground switch
            7233 at Central; PCB A-3 with a disconnect either side + ground switch 7243 at East
            Columbia. ~10 operable devices, 2 terminals. That is what 07 encodes.
            SECOND RULE, different publisher: 29 CFR 1910.269(n)(6), read at govinfo.gov. Attach the
            GROUND END FIRST then the line end; remove the LINE END FIRST then the ground end. The
            regulation states BOTH halves rather than saying "reverse", so both can be asserted.

            METHOD: TWO WORKERS, OPPOSITE INSTRUCTIONS, SAME ANSWER. One was told to start at OSHA,
            the other told explicitly NOT to and to start at utility switching manuals. They converged
            on the same document, same rule, same page, same worked example, and both independently
            found the same corroborator (Snohomish County PUD). Two different search paths landing on
            one document is evidence ABOUT THE DOCUMENT; one worker finding it twice would not be.
            Then everything the verify phase rests on was RE READ AT THE PUBLISHER by me, because a
            worker's honest grade is a warning and not a fix. Both workers' quotes and page labels
            survived exactly. Worker A's gaps section is the best this project has produced: it graded
