            🔴 THE CRUX FOR THE BUILD, from the gaps: BPA NEVER PRINTS A FILLED IN SWITCHING ORDER.
            86 pages, no numbered "Step 1 / Step 2" order form filled in anywhere. Both workers found
            this independently. So VERIFY ASSERTS THE RULE against a generated sequence, plus the prose
            example's stated device order. IT CANNOT DIFF AGAINST A PUBLISHED STEP LIST, because no
            step list is published. Do not let a future session claim otherwise.
            Real negative finding, from reading both IN FULL: Reclamation FIST 1-1 and 1-2 contain NO
            filled in worked switching order either. They reference an SPF form that carries the device
            sequence and only ever show it blank.

            TOOLING, worth keeping: WebFetch's summarizer REFUSED to quote public domain CFR verbatim
            (citing a copyright policy that does not apply to federal regulations) and misreported the
            FIST PDFs as corrupted when they are normal text layer PDFs. curl + PyMuPDF solved both.
            And the CFR text layer interleaves the PRINTER'S PAGE FURNITURE INTO THE MIDDLE OF A
            SENTENCE ("...before he or she VerDate Sep<11>2014 ... Jkt 262121 ... removes the ground-end
            connection"), and hyphenates across line breaks ("em- ployees") so a literal search for the
            paragraph heading finds NOTHING and a careless reader concludes the paragraph is absent.
            Same family as 02's flattened fraction bar: THE TEXT LAYER IS NOT THE DOCUMENT.

