            That is 02's "the manual agrees with itself three ways" in a different shape. Check C4
            exists to prove C3 is not vacuous: from the un-preceded state the verb really is
            different.

            🔴 THE MODEL FACT THAT MAKES IT WORK, AND BPA PROVES IT TWICE: LIMITS ARE TOPOLOGICAL,
            NOT STATEFUL. It is natural to compute limits against the live state (only count a device
            if something is live through it now). That is wrong. Ex 2's Line Side Disconnect is
            ALREADY OPEN and is still a published limit. Ex 5's ACB-1 is described in BPA's own words
            as "the open low voltage isolating device" and is still a published limit. A limit is not
            about what IS energizing the zone, it is about what COULD. The tag is the point, not the
            opening. Compute it statefully and Example 2's answer collapses to one device; BPA says
            two. Mutation tested.

