2026-07-17  ⚠ EXAMPLE 5 (P-51) DELIBERATELY NOT ENCODED, and the reason is the finding.
            It is the largest published answer in the document: FIVE limit devices, the only ones
            that cross a voltage class. "A-9 Transformer Side and Auxiliary Bus and B-2 Transformer
            Side and Auxiliary Bus Disconnect switches will be tagged as Clearance limits ... a Do
            Not Operate tag shall also be placed on the open low voltage isolating device ACB-1 as a
            Clearance limit."
            The figure was traced at 20x and most of it is solid: A-9 and B-2 mirror the Example 1
            arrangement exactly, and the trunk from the bank CROSSES the B main bus WITHOUT a
            junction dot, which is a crossover and not a connection (assume otherwise and the model
            shorts the transformer to the bus).
            WHAT IS NOT SOLID IS THE MECHANISM. BPA's purpose clause says ACB-1 is tagged to control
            energization of the clearance "from the alternate station service source". Reading the
            ATS at 22x: the pivot is the common, it feeds the Station Service Loads, and it selects
            between a normal contact (fed through ACB-1) and an alternate contact (fed from the
            alternate source). AN OPEN TRANSITION TRANSFER SWITCH NEVER JOINS THOSE TWO CONTACTS, so
            on the drawing as traced THE ALTERNATE SOURCE HAS NO PATH TO ACB-1, and the published
            rationale cannot be reproduced without assuming a transfer mechanism BPA never states.
            THE ANSWER IS PUBLISHED. THE PATH IS NOT. Encoding it means picking whichever ATS model
            makes BPA's published answer come out, which is an answer key grading itself (#21). So it
            stays out, written down, until the mechanism is found in the document or put to someone
            who runs one. Same shape as the rule's missing rationale (#26): assert what is published,
            decline to publish the physics in the source's voice.
            🔗 Worth noting for 03 and for IEM: this is an ATS question, and 03 already proved there
            is no "the" ATS. Whether this one parallels its sources on transfer is a VENDOR fact, and
            BPA does not name the vendor.
